==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hurdy-gurdy
<hw>Hur"dy-gur`dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. of
imitative origin.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A stringed instrument,
lutelike in shape, in which the sound is produced by the friction of a
wheel turned by a crank at the end, instead of by a bow, two of the
strings being tuned as drones, while two or more, tuned in unison, are
modulated by keys.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In California, a water wheel with radial buckets,
driven by the impact of a jet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hurkaru</ent>⟦br⟧
